description:
Diceman was a bi-monthly comic spin-off from 2000AD, which ran for five issues in 1986 (February to October).

It was capitalising on the then craze for fighting fantasy/choose your own adventure style gamebooks, where the reader had to decide on what the character should do next at the end of each panel or section.

Pat Mills wrote the majority of the stories/adventures and many regular 2000AD characters appeared, including Judge Dredd, Rogue Trooper, Slaine, Nemesis the Warlock and the ABC Warriors.

Rick Fortune (the 'Diceman') was a new character especially created for the comic and his adventures ran from the second issue until the fifth and final issue.
name: Diceman

description: After being cancelled in 1984 after only 15 issues, Scream rose from the dead once more in these annual summer specials (four Holiday Specials were produced between 1985-1988 and one Spinechillers Special in 1989). The specials contained a mix of new and reprint strips plus readers drawings, photo features (usually the London Dungeon) and games.
name: Scream! Holiday Special

description:
After 15 issues and four previous specials, Scream finally went to its grave in this fifth and final holiday special from 1989.

Spinechillers features all new stories and characters, even the old editor Ghastly McNasty has been usurped by a new villainous narrator - 'Ghoul' (who had presented a one-off story the previous year in Eagle 343).
name: Scream! Spinechillers Holiday Special

Reading Order

  1. Batman: Arkham City
  2. Batman: Arkham City Digital Chapters
  3. This volume

Reprinting 3 digital stories per issue.

  • Issue #6: Theater of Violence (#14-16)
  • Issue #7: Arkham City Sirens (#17-19)

  • Issue #12: Repentance (#32-34)
  • Issue #13: Eviction Notice (#35-37)
  • Issue #14: Beloved (#38-40)
  • Issue #15: Uninvited Guests (#41-43)
    Release Date: June 12, 2013
  • Issue #16: Welcome to the Slough of Despond (#44-46)
    Release Date: July 10, 2013

Collected Editions / Hardcover

Reprinting 15 digital stories or 5 print copies per volume.

  • Volume 1 (digital issues #1-13; or print issues #1-5)*
  • Volume 2 (digital issues #14-28; or print issues #6-10)
    Release Date: August 7, 2013

* Volume 1 also includes Batman: Arkham City Digital Chapters #6-7.

Writers Claudio Sanchez and Chondra Echert (KILL AUDIO) bring a deadly new vision of New York City in KEY OF Z, with stunning artwork by Aaron Kuder (THE AMORY WARS). The zombie apocalypse has transformed the city into two separate battle-hardened fiefdoms. Nick Ewing is left to survive while seeking revenge on those responsible for the death of his family – the warring gangs residing in The Big Apple’s most illustrious athletic houses. Ewing stumbles upon a sentimental artifact from his past that imbues him with surprising power. Find out what happens when he discovers the KEY OF Z.

Collected in Key Of Z.
